column1: Congratulations to @JoeBiden and @KamalaHarris our next President and Vice President of the United States.   I have no doubt they have what it takes to restore the soul of America and tackle the challenges that lie ahead.

Thank you #OH11!   I am honored to have earned your trust for another term.    I look forward to continue working in Congress on behalf of everyone in Ohio’s 11th Congressional District. https://t.co/sDkAjcLSSQ
It’s Election Day and polls are open until 7:30 pm.  Find your polling location here: https://t.co/k5wbjp4BaZ  Your VOTE is your VOICE.

1 day.  Ohio voters here are the options for making your voice heard:  1. Vote early in person before 2 pm today.  2. Return your absentee ballot by 7:30 pm tomorrow.  3. Vote in person on Election Day.  For times and voting & drop box locations visit: https://t.co/bmMXryE3vt
Proud to welcome our next Vice President @KamalaHarris to Northeast Ohio today.   #BidenHarris2020   https://t.co/NyBkNXtMOx
10 days.  VOTE. https://t.co/R0PJNYVf9y
20 days.  VOTE. https://t.co/R0PJNYVf9y

Second round of stimulus checks. Extended unemployment benefits. Boost to SNAP. Funding for testing. Education & child care support. Rental assistance. USPS funding.   The President is blocking all of this so the Senate can rush through his Supreme Court nominee.  Vote.

On February 7 the President told Bob Woodward that COVID-19 was “more deadly than even your strenuous flu” even as he publicly downplayed the virus.  Eight months and more than 210000 deaths later the President is still lying to the American people.
Your vote is your voice.  Today is the first day of early voting in Ohio.  Make a plan to vote today by visiting https://t.co/KJPrMUsCV7.

After requiring stimulus checks to be sent out with his signature the President is mandating that food boxes for struggling families include a letter from him.  The “master marketer” is marketing himself using federal resources. https://t.co/Lh4ecdtigD
Shocking but not surprising: The President is the single largest driver of coronavirus misinformation.   #FailureToLead https://t.co/EHaHcJLyf8

Today at 6:00 PM EDT I will be moderating a panel of activists on the importance of making our voices heard at the ballot box this November.   Tune in at 6:00 PM by visiting https://t.co/XjJZQdIRWz  #CBCFALC2020 #OurVotesMatter https://t.co/9CCbpZqurA
Say her name.   #JusticeForBreonnaTaylor
If Republicans had an agenda that the majority of Americans supported they would work to expand voting not suppress it.

On National Voter Registration Day make sure you are #VoteReady. Visit https://t.co/TtTq5uQNbx to register and make a plan to vote.  Early voting begins in Ohio in just 2 WEEKS.  Your vote and your voice matter.

Join me tomorrow for a conversation about the power of our votes and voices as we work to address the economic and racial injustices that have plagued our community and our country for far too long.  Tune in tomorrow at 3:30 PM EST by visiting https://t.co/CaAzqXQZEQ https://t.co/w0dGQGxjrM
The nomination of @KamalaHarris as Vice President is one of the most exciting things that has happened in our party and our country for a very long time. https://t.co/N65i727XDn
Election Day starts today.  If we want to turn Ohio blue we need to treat every day from this day forward as Election Day.

The right to vote is sacred but the struggle to secure that Constitutional right continues to this day.  ALL IN: The Fight For Democracy is an inside look at voter suppression in the U.S.   @allinthefilm comes to Prime Video on 9/18.  #AllInForVoting  https://t.co/UNd7evd6xQ
Shirley Chisholm would be proud. #BlackWomenLead https://t.co/yQZaeOGHhY

Congratulations to @JoeBiden on an excellent choice and to @KamalaHarris for making history by becoming the first Black woman to be a major-party vice-presidential nominee.   #BlackWomenLead #BidenHarris2020 https://t.co/xsRBNT8dHe

In Ohio and nationwide @JoeBiden is better for Black business.  Read my latest on how the former Vice President’s common-sense plans will support Black entrepreneurs and small businesses as they recover and look to the future. https://t.co/fuXUJFAxQa

Tearing down the walls of racism means marching together toward a better future. @JoeBiden has always fought for the dignity & opportunity everyone deserves. His #BuildBackBetter plan makes clear that racial equity is key to recovering economically & marching forward as a nation. https://t.co/a32AJlXOAi
Congrats to @JoyAnnReid on this well-deserved trailblazing achievement. https://t.co/cFK8vRPoTZ

Today the Education Unity Task Force unveiled its recommendations that build on @JoeBiden's vision to bring transformative change to our educational system.    We must ensure that every child everywhere is able to receive a world-class education. https://t.co/NossDPPUf0
Congratulations to @EmiliaSykesOH for being named the winner of this year’s @emilyslist Gabby Giffords Rising Star Award! https://t.co/uWyLTJdnRP

Proud to stand with Councilman @basheerj and local leaders yesterday to speak out against injustice and demand change. https://t.co/Om7ixAtMbo

Proud to announce I will help lead the new Education Unity Task Force.   Looking forward to working with @HeatherGautney and the other members of the task force to help @JoeBiden ensure quality equitable education is available to all. https://t.co/CJRE42Oqdy
Thank you to the great people of the 11th Congressional District of Ohio for your support in the primary election!!  It is an honor to serve you! #11thCongressionalDistrict #OH11 #ohdem

If you requested an absentee ballot by the April 25 deadline but have not yet received it you can vote provisionally at your Board of Elections. Remember to take precautions and practice social distancing. (2/2)
ATTENTION OHIO VOTERS: There is still time to drop off your absentee ballot.   You have until 7:30 PM TONIGHT to return your absentee ballot to a drop box at your local Board of Elections. (1/2)

The Black community has been hit hard by the coronavirus.  Today I am joining @KamalaHarris and Black community leaders for a town hall moderated by @SymoneDSanders on #COVID19 disparities & @JoeBiden’s plan to address them.  Tune in at 3:30 PM: https://t.co/xfCdQ9vBSI

🚨 Attention Ohio Voters 🚨   Today is the LAST DAY to postmark and mail in your absentee ballot.  You can also drop your ballot off TOMORROW at your local board of elections no later than 7:30 p.m.  Make sure your friends and family are aware of these deadlines!
